Description:
Studio-A  Automazione  is  an  italian  competitive,  skilled  and  constantly  growing  Company  operating worldwide since 2006 and active in the following market:

•	Oil & Gas;  
•	Refining and Petrochemical;  
•	Cement production;  
•	Chemical and pharmaceutical;  
•	Power generation;  
•	Waste treatment;  
•	Water and sewage treatment.  

Company’s original structure (Instrument, Control & Safety System Engineering and Supply) has  been further integrated with a Plant & Package Division to provide supply of preassembled Skid- mounted Process/Utility units as well as EPC project (turn-key).  
Plant & Package Division is a completely autonomous branch from the executive point of view  and works in close coordination with headquarter representing it in all respects.   
It  is  also  the  point  of  contact  for  Customers  located  in  Northern/Central  Italy  as  well  for  our  International Clients.  

Studio-A is certified according to UNI EN ISO 9001 quality standard. 

Thanks to our experience in Automation, many EPC contracts for the Engineering and Supply of  complete Control & Safety Systems have been acquired and completed by Studio-A automazione  all over the years, many project starting from a reverse engineering of the obsolete automation  systems (in case of lack of existing documentation) up to the commissioning and start-up of the  newly installed System.

FutureLab LLC - innovative company engaged in research and development in the field of robotics and automation. The company has been founded in 2011 and located in Russia, Yekaterinburg city. Also we based in Riyadh and working with Saudi companies

The main product of the company is CableWalker - a robotic system for monitoring and maintenance of OHPL and Telecom sector.

CableWalker - An innovative digital robotic device for monitoring and maintaining power lines in real time, improving the efficiency of power grids.

CableWalker - automatic maintenance system for electrical networks that allows:
• docking the CableWalker drone to a power line operating from 10 to 220 kW;
• providing the best diagnostics of overhead power lines
• providing maintenance, wire lubrication, installation and removal of special devices on wires
• charging batteries from the power lines

➢ The technology makes it possible to switch from scheduled preventive repairs to condition-based repairs, save money and make accurate investments in specific problem areas.

➢ The CableWalker technology provides:
• the best possible quality of monitoring, maintenance and repair of elements of electric networks;
• absolute safety and better opportunities for staff;
• cardinal improvement in the quality of manageability, efficiency, reliability;
• increase of efficiency of the power network enterprise up, reduction of asset ownership cost by 25%;
• possibility to organize an automatic system of maintenance and repair of electric networks.

Join us in shaping the future of robotics. Follow FutureLab on LinkedIn for the latest updates, industry insights and career opportunities.

