ROBOSECT is a technology-driven company founded in 2024 in Bologna, Italy.
Its core technology is based on years of research conducted at the Laboratory of Automation and Robotics (LAR) at the University of Bologna.
ROBOSECT is a spin-off project of the University of Bologna.

Key competencies/services:

- Robotic applications that require the manipulation and/or perception of flexible and deformable elements such as electrical cables and similar items;
- Development of algorithms for the automated assembly of electrical panels and control panels, and more generally the production of components containing electrical cables and other deformable elements;
- AI-based vision solutions for industrial scenarios;
- Research and development in the field of robotics, deformable objects, and deep learning;

